  "texts": [
    "To the best of our knowledge, this study is the first attempt to compare multiple open-source LLMs in echocardiography report summarization through different model adaptation methods.",
    "Trained on one of the largest echocardiography report datasets in the world, we demonstrated that QLoRA fine-tuning can significantly improve LLMs' performance for the desired summarization task, with at least comparable qualities to human experts.",
    "Our results also indicate that ICL is associated with significant limitations for clinical practice, including compromised patient privacy and report quality.",
    "Additionally, we demonstrated that current automatic metrics are not sensitive to the change in measurement numbers in echo reports.",
    "The current study provides insights into the construction of a dedicated local LLM for echo report summarization and can pave the way for an AI-enabled echocardiography interpretation system with a human-AI interaction interface."
  ],
